article.headline: Oklahoma St. 83, Savannah St. 56
article.story: STILLWATER, Okla. -- James Anderson scored 23 points to help lead Oklahoma State to an 83-56 victory over Savannah State on Tuesday night. Anderson scored in double figures for the 13th time in 14 games this season. He also pulled down seven rebounds for the Cowboys (11-3), who have now won six in a row. Obi Muonelo added 17 points and Byron Eaton had 16. Chris Linton scored 16 points for Savannah State (7-8). Rashad Hassan scored 12 points and Raye Bailey added 11 for the Tigers, who lost their fourth consecutive game. Savannah State trailed 48-36 with 13:37 to play but were outscored 30-13 over the next 10 minutes.
